<h1>LINKS is a global community for cardiovascular health</h1>

<p class="intro"><a href="http://www.linkscommunity.org">LINKS</a> provides resources, support and networking opportunities that support country programs for cardiovascular health. Membership in the LINKS community is free and is designed for those working to improve cardiovascular health in developing global settings.</p>

<p>Join the community for exclusive access to:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Peer-to-peer contact</li>
    <li>Participation in webinars</li>
    <li>Opportunity to apply for technical assistance or funding support to eligible programs</li>
</ol>

<p>Learn more at: <a href="http://www.linkscommunity.org">LINKScommunity.org</a></p>

<h2>Who is behind LINKS?</h2>
<p>LINKS is a collaborative effort of the World Health Organization, the CDC Foundation, and Resolve to Save Lives, an initiative of Vital Strategies.</p>

